Package: wallet-cli
Version: 0.1.0-1
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: SIROS Foundation <info@siros.org>
Installed-Size: 15228
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.34), init-system-helpers (>= 1.52), libfido2-1
Recommends: pinentry-gnome3 | pinentry-gtk-3 | pinentry-qt | pinentry
Suggests: yubikey-manager
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/sirosfoundation/go-siros-cli
Description: SIROS Wallet CLI - Verifiable credentials wallet
 wallet-cli is a command-line tool for managing verifiable credentials
 using hardware-backed security keys (FIDO2/WebAuthn).
 .
 Features:
  - Hardware-backed key storage using FIDO2 PRF extension
  - Issue and present verifiable credentials
  - OpenID for Verifiable Credentials (OID4VC) support
  - Background daemon with MCP server for AI assistant integration
  - Pinentry-based user approval for sensitive operations
